# Bandit Level 9 → Level 10

## Objective
The goal of this level was to find the password for the next level.  
The password was stored in the file `data.txt` in one of the few human-readable strings, preceded by several `=` characters.

---

## Challenge
This level was more confusing because the file contained mostly unreadable or binary data.

At first, I experimented with several commands to try and identify readable text or lines containing the `=` character.

Some of the commands I tried included:

sort data.txt | strings "="

file data.txt | grep "="

grep "ASCII" data.txt

However, these attempts did not return the correct result.

Through experimenting, I realised that the important clue in the challenge was the phrase “human-readable strings”. This led me to understand that I needed to extract readable text from the file first before searching for the `=` symbols.

---

## Steps I Took

I used the following command:

strings data.txt | grep "="

This command extracted readable text strings from the file and then searched for lines containing the `=` character.

The output displayed the password for the next level.

---

## Password for Level 10
FGUW5ilLVJrxX9kMYMmlN4MgbpfMiqey

---

## Commands Learned

### strings
The `strings` command extracts human-readable text from binary or unreadable files.

### grep
The `grep` command searches for specific text patterns inside input or files.

### |
The pipe symbol (`|`) sends the output of one command into another command.

### strings data.txt | grep "="
This command extracted readable strings from the file and filtered the lines containing `=` characters.
